This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as rumour stance classification. It also involves the analysis of Twitter conversations, which falls under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Social Computing (cs.SOC) sub-categories. The use of tree-structured conversation threads suggests that it could also be relevant to the Structured Data (cs.SD) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which could place it under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
